{"cursor":"19480","size":15,"audio":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/2/20/Halo2_last_spartan.ogg"],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox album |  Name = Volumes\nOne and Two\n| Type =soundtrack Artist = Various Artists Cover = Halo2-ost-volumes.png\n| Released = November 9, 2004 (Vol. 1) April 25, 2006 (Vol. 2) Recorded =\n|  Length = 69:20 (Vol. 1) 68:48 (Vol. 2) Label = Sumthing Else Music Works Producer = Nile Rodgers\n}}\n\nThe 'Halo 2 Original Soundtrack' is the soundtrack for Bungie's 2004 video game\n[[Halo 2]]. The soundtrack was released as two separate volumes, released almost\ntwo years apart. Volume 1, released at the same time as Halo 2 on November 9,\n2004, contains arranged instrumental pieces written by Martin O'Donnell and his\npartner Michael Salvatori, as well as \"inspired by\" tracks from bands Incubus,\nHoobastank and Breaking Benjamin. Volume 2 was released on April 25, 2006 and\ncontains all the game music arranged in a suite form.\n\nO'Donnell, who had previously composed the music for Bungie games such as\n[[Myth (series)|Myth]] and [[Halo: Combat Evolved]], sought to develop the\n\"Halo sound\" of the previous game as well as introduce new sounds and\ninfluences to the music. The music was based on what was happening in the game,\nrather than using leitmotifs or theme repetitively. The music was recorded in\npieces with a fifty-piece orchestra at Studio X in Seattle, Washington. To mark\nits release both Microsoft and Sumthing Else Music Works planned an aggressive\nmarketing campaign.\n\nUpon release, the music of Halo 2 was well received. Critics were split on the\nmerits of Volume 1, with some publications enjoying the bonus offerings while\nothers felt the first volume lacked cohesion. Volume 2 was declared the \"real\"\nsoundtrack to Halo 2. Upon release both soundtracks became commercial successes,\nwith more than 100,000 copies sold. The soundtracks' success was pointed to as a\nsign of increasing legitimacy of video game music in the entertainment industry.\nHalos music has since been played in concert settings, including [[Play! A Video\nGame Symphony]] and [[Video Games Live]].\n","linknr":313,"url":"Connected_(Hoobastank_song)","recorded":1374543604,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Halo_2_Original_Soundtrack&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Halo_2_Original_Soundtrack&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Halo_2_Original_Soundtrack","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=Connected_(Hoobastank_song)&redirect=no","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:Halo2-ost-volumes.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/c5/Halo2-ost-volumes.png/220px-Halo2-ost-volumes.png","/wiki/Soundtrack_album","/wiki/Record_label","/wiki/Sumthing_Else_Music_Works","/wiki/Record_producer","/wiki/Nile_Rodgers","/wiki/Bungie","/wiki/2004_in_video_gaming","/wiki/Video_game","/wiki/Halo_2","/wiki/Martin_O%27Donnell","/wiki/Michael_Salvatori","/wiki/Incubus_(band)","/wiki/Hoobastank","/wiki/Breaking_Benjamin","/wiki/Suite_(music)","/wiki/Myth_(series)","/wiki/Halo:_Combat_Evolved","/wiki/Leitmotif","/wiki/Seattle,_Washington","/wiki/Video_game_music","/wiki/Play!_A_Video_Game_Symphony","/wiki/Video_Games_Live","#Background","#Promotion","#Reception","#Track_listings","#Volume_1","#V